First off, let me say the actual concept and puzzles are excellent, 10/10. However, I can't understand why the play button is in the bottom middle of the screen. My s10+ has a ~2k display, but I don't think this game even runs at 1080p. Looks noticibly pixelated.

content: This game is amazing. It's very polished. The most important thing is that the levels are all designed beautifully. Each one you pass leads you to new ones that are just outside your skill level. You have to genuinely think very deeply to come up with solutions. It's the perfect challenge. You'll think you're beat, and then you'll return with a fresh perspective and you'll figure it out. It's a real challenge, but it's ultimately fair. That makes it worth the time you end up putting in.
Lots of fun! Challenging too! Graphics are adorable.

Not sure what all the fuss is about. The graphics are quite cute and the puzzle element is ok (not my bag) but it's not 'amazing' by any stretch. Definitely not worth the half price I paid for it in the sale. If you are rich give it a go, but there are better free puzzle games out there.
Damn you Alan

content: One of the best puzzle games i know. The premisse is simple (pick up & deliver aliens), but hard to execute. Be prepared for a lot of "oh, this is simple, I'll just ...wait ...I'm stuck" moments. The puzzles are elegant, though: they just need the right approach. which makes it all the more rewarding once you've finished a level . All in all : highly recommended (hint : so are the author's other games :-) ).
well crafted puzzles, stunning graphics and hundreds of levels with unique fun elements. buy it for its full price, its worth it.
I hate this game so much. It's so good. It lured me in with easy opening levels, and then destroyed me.

brilliant, charming, challenging, fair. simple looking puzzles using simple mechanics that require complex solutions. the epitome of good puzzle game design.

great puzzle game! reminiscent of another one of my favorites, trainyard. only downside is that the "reset" button looks like an "undo" button, and I hit it all the time just wanting to undo a single track placement but losing everything I've worked out. but that's a small detail, overall the game is one of the best I've found on Android

Great game had it in my wishlist for awhile and finally pulled the trigger 
today. Really sucks you right in, surprised more people haven't dloaded 
this since its totally addictive and really fun. Just buy it, totally worth 
it and you'll love ease of play and challenge present on each level.

I am not a big gamer, but this is hands down the greatest game I ever 
played. Found it completely by accident. Cannot believe it only has 1000 GP 
downloads - it deserves to dominate the charts. Treat yourself to this game 
- the design of the levels is incredibly poetic and, in its most intense 
moments, you'll learn something about yourself and/or life. Kudos to the 
team that made it!

One of the best puzzlegames I played. It will keep you challenged for many 
hours. Especially the later zones and the secret levels are complicated. 
But it never forces you to do the hard levels, you can also take a break on 
an easier path for a while.

Elegant puzzle, worth every penny. Kudos to the developer team! Just don't 
give up solving it and the shortest path is always guaranteed to be wrong.
Don't let the graphics fool you, this game is not easy. But for those up to the challenge there is a lot to discover here.
I'm 20 puzzles in and so far this has been a great puzzle game! will update as I go.

Probably the best game I have bought on the play store. The graphics look great on the phone and appeals to all age ranges. Love the fact that there is no adverts just pay your money and enjoy the game. This should have 1 million plus downloads not just 1000.

I've been a fan since I discovered A Good Snowman and Sokobond, and Cosmic Express certainly doesn't disappoint! The art style is incredibly well done and the mechanics are simple yet very clever, with just enough open-endedness to really give you that awesome satisfaction of having worked out a problem yourself. Strongly recommend to anyone looking for a great, high quality puzzle game!
Not a bad puzzler. The only issue I have is that it warms my phone up after playing for a while.
Great game. Love the art style, sound and graphics are great. Puzzles are challenging. Works well on tablet and mobile.
replyContent: Hi Marc! Cloud saving is already in the game: just go to options - progress - cloud save. It's not enabled by default because it requires you to log in to enable it. Glad you're enjoying the game!

Cosmic Express is such a simple, smart, cute and fiendish little puzzler with some real surprises up its sleeve. It's non-linear so when you get stuck (there's no if!) you can have a break and try different puzzles. It works perfectly on your phone and is worth every penny.

replyContent: Hi, glad you're enjoying the game! I know that behaviour seems weird, but I promise it'll become clear when you find other levels that do the same thing, or spot what's different about that level.

Alan is a friend of mine, so obviously I'm biased. But I really love his games. As objectively as I can, I think they feature a lot of character and puzzles that will melt your mind, along with some amazing secret stuff that's even harder. This one's wonderful, and a step up in size, graphics, and sound from A Good Snowman is Hard to Build, with the same great attention to how the brain figures out puzzles and deep exploration of what's possible given a set of puzzle rules.
